  "text": "The compliance rate may be another critical factor affecting sputum conversion during the early period of treatment. Concomitant prescription of at least five anti-TB drugs and a relatively high incidence of secondary anti-TB drug-associated side effects can cause low compliance. In addition, drug concentration and pharmacokinetic variability of anti-TB drugs [CITATION_1] as well as drug compliance [CITATION_2] can influence treatment failure and drug resistance acquisition in TB patients, as TB has microbial, clinical, and programmatic causes. In our in PTH, and 71.2% in CS. Although the clinical meaning of these results remains uncertain, they warrant a larger prospective study that includes scheduled multiple time samplings to determine the role of TDM in MDR-TB patients.",
